cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a method for explaining the outcome of a classification black-box, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method uses gradient information, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the preservation of features unrelated to the classification decision, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer security (cs.CR).
